[Setup] add configuration, branding-info and quick-install button (#120)

The quick-install button for Oomph contains the following URL:
https://www.eclipse.org/setups/installer/?url=https://raw.githubusercontent.com/eclipse-m2e/m2e-core/master/setup/m2eDevelopmentEnvironmentConfiguration.setup&show=true

Effectively this points to the configuration added with this commit.

[Doc] improve README, CONTRIBUTING and Oomph-setup button (#264)

* [Doc] improve README, CONTRIBUTING and rendering of links as buttons

The statement about a required signed-off phrase
in the commit message of non-committer contributions is removed, because
it is not required anymore (see
https://bugs.eclipse.org/bugs/show_bug.cgi?id=558653#c30 )

Also add shields.io badges for Version, License, Build and Tests state
of m2e.

* [SQUASH] fix typo to 'about'
[Doc] cosmetic improvements of buttons in doc (#265)

[Build] improve snapshot deployment (remove <version>/latest and clear) (#467)

- remove 'latest' sub-folder for snapshot repo for specific version to
align better with snapshots/latest
- completely clear download.e.o/tech/m2e/snapshots before snapshot
deployment to remove old versions automatically
- inline only once used variables

- add a note about the verison-specific snapshot repo in README.md

Publish p2 repo to GH

Signed-off-by: Fred Bricon <fbricon@gmail.com>

Fine tune p2 publishing process

- CI builds on master are automatically published to https://jbosstools.github.io/m2e-apt/snapshots/
- Release builds require pushing a tag following the vVERSION format (eg. v1.5.4). Update sites will then be published to:
   * https://jbosstools.github.io/m2e-apt/latest/
   * https://jbosstools.github.io/m2e-apt/updates/VERSION
